org.chronos.chronosphere.internal.ogm.api

Interface EPackageBundle

  • All Superinterfaces:
    java.lang.Iterable<org.eclipse.emf.ecore.EPackage>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    EPackageBundleImpl

    public interface EPackageBundle
extends java.lang.Iterable<org.eclipse.emf.ecore.EPackage>
    An EPackageBundle is a collection of EPackages that is self-contained, i.e. does not reference any elements that are not contained in the bundle.

    The EcorePackage is an implicit member of any EPackageBundle. It will not be contained in getContents(), and will not be returned by the iterator.

      • containsEPackageWithNsURI

        default boolean containsEPackageWithNsURI(java.lang.String ePackageNsURI)
        Checks if this bundle contains an EPackage with the given namespace URI.

        This method will only check the root-level EPackages, sub-packages will not be checked.

        Parameters:
        ePackageNsURI - The namespace URI to find. Must not be null.
        Returns:
        true if this bundle contains an EPackage with the given namespace URI, otherwise false.

      • getEPackageByNsURI

        org.eclipse.emf.ecore.EPackage getEPackageByNsURI(java.lang.String ePackageNsURI)
        Returns a contained EPackage by its namespace URI.

        This method will only check the root-level EPackages, sub-packages will not be checked.

        Parameters:
        ePackageNsURI - The namespace URI to get the EPackage for. Must not be null.
        Returns:
        The EPackage with the given namespace URI, or null if this bundle contains no such EPackage.
